@NickeNyfiken66:
I rarely ever have access to the DVDs in any other language other than English (That I know of), but can't you select the language you want at the beginning of the install?

@pwrs33d3r:
Thank you for posting regarding this - I just wish more people would be as considerate as you!

@jesusman82:
I have installed Windows 7 on clients' computers many times (Dells), and only had problems a couple of times, and it was because of the memory size - You should try to have at LEAST 4GB of FREE RAM at all times for Windows 7, but turning off certain things like the Aero theme, indexing, etc may prevent the OS from sucking up all your RAM ...

@muttdammit:
You will have the option to either 'Upgrade' (Does NOT delete/format), or 'Clean Install' (Which DOES format) - No backup? Choose 'Upgrade' ;-)

@gur0ch4m:
Since this is a copy of a 'straight to company' DVD, there is also a pre-activated (Legal OEM) choice when installing (I never use 'pre-activated' OSs - The DVD I copied was intended for package Asus builds from the manufacturer) - Yes, Microsoft DOES ship pre-activated OEMs!

@CjnaNujpS:
Yes, you can do a full repair/restore with this - I had to when I tried installing Linux Mint as a dual-boot with this, and the GRUB loader prevented Windows from booting - Did a repair via USB with this, and it got fixed easily ...

@Julioso:
MAC addresses NEVER change, unless you get a whole new computer - IPs are 'hit or miss', but MAC addresses can't be 'hidden' or changed - I only did that to the people that downloaded the whole thing, and only uploaded less than 200MB ...

@Accolon9:
It's not difficult o.O
There are MANY programs that can scan for the MAC address for any given IP - They run in real-time, so when an IP connects, it is logged on a GUI - Once you have the MAC address, all you need to do is block it from connecting to your router :-D

@Accolon9:
It's not that difficult o.O
There's a lot of programs out there that can get the MAC address from any IP that connects to it, and display it, then just block the MAC in your router ...

@sofmarmic:
Thanks for posting that this worked! :-)

@djrush:
I have a RAID setup with this, and I haven't had any problems with it so far ...

@Val777:
I installed this the day I copied the DVDs, and I am activated - The Loader modifies the SLIC and WAT entries at boot-level, so it does not get 'noticed' - I don't know where you get your information from, but I suggest you research what the Loader does, and stop trolling o.O
